"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76449","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-17","<p>Currently there are no prisoners convicted of terrorist-related offences held in open conditions.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-07-17T14:33:22.4517522Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76449/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76449/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-08","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners convicted of terrorist-related offences are held in open prisons.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","204456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76450","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-09-01","<p>To identify how many prisoners have absconded on more than one occasion in the last twenty years, or the highest number of absconds by an individual, would require a manual examination of the prison record of every prisoner who had absconded in this time frame. This could only be achieved at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>As a result of improved risk assessment procedures the number of prisoners absconding from open prisons has reduced significantly over the last 10 years. There were 225 absconds in 2013-14 compared to 1,301 in 2003-04.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","204502","2014-09-01T10:46:21.6093867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76450/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76450/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-08","Prisoner Escapes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the highest number of absconds from prison by an individual offender has been in the last 20 years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","204457"
