"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76473","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-14","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Information Commissioner has regular discussions with the Secretary of State for Justice and other Ministry of Justice Ministers about a range of information rights issues. However, I am not aware that he has raised data protection and freedom of information issues relating to Sussex Police's promotion of Operation Crackdown during the course of these discussions.</p><p> </p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-07-14T14:23:56.0334947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76473/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76473/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-08","Road Traffic Offences: Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what advice he has taken from the Information Commissioner's Office about data protection and freedom of information issues arising from Sussex Police's promotion of the Operation Crackdown.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","204604"
