missioners. With their knowledge of local victims' needs and priorities, PCCs are uniquely placed to ensure that funding is targeted according to need.</p><p> </p><p>Individual victims and survivors of Northern-Ireland related acts of terrorism who are resident in England and Wales are able to apply for funding from the Victims and Survivors Service (VSS) in Northern Ireland. The VSS is the main funder of victims' groups in Northern Ireland and provides a tailored package to meet the individual needs of victims and survivors including counselling, physiotherapy and the purchase of equipment such as wheelchairs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-07-16T14:11:34.4116204Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76509/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76509/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-08","Terrorism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what support the Government provides to victims and survivors of Northern Ireland-related acts of terrorism in Great Britain; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Hoey","Vauxhall","Kate Hoey","204449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76510","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-15","<p>I can confirm that the Government has not commissioned specific research into victims and survivors of Northern Ireland-related acts of terrorism who reside inGreat Britain. In 2012 the Ministry of Justice commissioned and published an Evidence and Practice Review which looked in depth at the needs of victims inEngland andWales. This has informed both the commissioning approach to national services for victims such as the Homicide Service and the development of an outcomes-based commissioning framework to be drawn upon by Police and Crime Commissioners when commissioning local services for victims.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises that victims of the most serious crimes should receive enhanced entitlements to support from the Criminal Justice organisations in England and Wales, and this is set out in the Code of Practice for Victims of Crime published in October 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes","204451","2014-07-15T16:42:25.4212692Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76510/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76510/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-08","Terrorism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate the Government has made of the number of victims and survivors of Northern Ireland-related acts of terrorism in Great Britain where such victims and survivors live in Great Britain; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Hoey","Vauxhall","Kate Hoey","204450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76511","Prime Minister","false","2014-07-14","<p>I last met Prime Minister Simpson Miller of Jamaica in July 2012 during HM The Queen's reception to mark the opening of the Olympic Games. I do not currently have plans for a future meeting. I met Caribbean Foreign Ministers at the UK-Caribbean Ministerial Forum hosted by the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) on 16-17 June.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2014-07-14T11:52:58.5474052Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76511/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76511/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-07-08","Jamaica","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when he last met the Prime Minister of Jamaica; and when he next plans to meet her.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","204495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76512","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>The Traffic Signs Regulations and General Directions (2002) prescribes a traffic sign for indicating the distance ahead to a named motorway service and which permits the price per litre of unleaded petrol to be displayed. The Government also announced in October 2013 that it would trial the display of comparative fuel prices on traffic signs along a motorway route to better inform road users and to encourage competition. A feasibility study is currently in progress to enable the trial to be undertaken in 2015/16.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-07-15T12:42:44.8436968Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76512/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76512/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","Garages and Petrol Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to require service stations to advertise their fuel prices so that they are visible from the highway so that motorists know them before leaving the public carriageway.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","204488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76513","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>By 2015 the Access for All programme will have spent over £400m providing accessible routes at more than 150 stations since its launch in 2006. An additional £100m, to fund a further 42 projects up to 2019, was allocated in April 2014. More than 1,100 stations have also benefitted from smaller scale access improvements under the programme. Many of these projects have been at rural stations and are over and above accessibility improvements delivered as part of other station infrastructure works.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T15:55:38.0568278Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76513/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76513/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","Railway Stations: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure disabled rail users can access all platforms at rural stations.","false","Biography information for Richard Benyon","Newbury","Richard Benyon","204417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76514","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>A key element of the Government's strategy for the railways is improving connectivity to support economic growth - facilitating business, commuting and leisure journeys.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Projects and programmes that are set to improve connectivity between the north of England and Scotland by increasing capacity, reducing journey times, and/or improving performance or train frequencies include:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(a)Electrification in the North West of England – ten brand new four-coach electric trains commenced operation on the route between Manchester Airport and Edinburgh/Glasgow in May this year;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(b)The refranchising programme – including a recent Direct Award to Virgin West Coast Trains and award of the next InterCity East Coast franchise later this year and the next TransPennine Express franchise in 2015;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(c)HS2 – as announced in November last year, the Department is undertaking a study in collaboration with the Scottish Government to identify the broad options available to make further capacity and journey time improvements between northern England and Scotland.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T16:01:11.172424Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76514/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76514/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76514/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","Railways: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to improve rail connections from northern England to Scotland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Iain McKenzie","Inverclyde","Iain McKenzie","204599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76515","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The procurement of new trains, comprising 68 new vehicles, is being carried out by NXET Trains Limited under European Union Procurement Regulations and has not yet begun. Decisions about this procurement are a commercial matter for the operator.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T15:54:24.6364547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76515/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76515/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the (a) funding and (b) ownership arrangements are for the 17 new trains to be introduced on the Essex Thameside line under the terms of the new franchise agreement with NXET Trains Ltd; and what the deadline is for the introduction into service of the new fleet.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","204534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76516","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The standstill period for the Essex Thameside franchise competition has not yet concluded, as such the Department has not signed the new Franchise Agreement and we are not able to confirm this information at this time. An announcement will be made shortly once the Agreement has been signed. Rolling stock maintenance will be a matter for the franchisee.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T15:53:26.7165421Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76516/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76516/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the rolling stock maintenance arrangements will be for the franchise agreement with NXET Trains Ltd for rail passenger services on the Essex Thameside line.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","204533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76517","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>The following figures have been provided by the British Transport Police and cover all offences committed on the national rail network, the London Underground and other parts of the network which come under their jurisdiction.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><p> </p></td><td><p>2011-12</p><p> </p></td><td><p>2012-13</p><p> </p></td><td><p>2013-14</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of assaults on staff</p><p> </p></td><td><p>1,764</p><p> </p></td><td><p>1,729</p><p> </p></td><td><p>1,607</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of assaults on customers</p><p> </p></td><td><p>3,800</p><p> </p></td><td><p>3,832</p><p> </p></td><td><p>3,865</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p /> <p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The Department does not hold equivalent data for offences committed on other parts of the transport network which would be the responsibility of the relevant local constabulary.</p><p /> <p> </p><p />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-07-15T11:46:08.2319712Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76517/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76517/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76517/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","Public Transport: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of assaults on (a) staff and (b) customers on public transport in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","204526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76518","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport will work with the railway industry to establish a fund that will prioritise improved mobile communications on metropolitan and commuter train services into major cities across the country.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-07-15T11:43:11.8324488Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76518/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76518/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76518/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","Railways: Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on which rail lines and services broadband improvements will be financed from the £53.1 million fine imposed on Network Rail by the Office of Rail Regulation.","false","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","204506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76519","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The procurement of new trains is being carried out by NXET Trains Limited under European Union Procurement Regulations and has not yet begun. Decisions about this procurement are a commercial matter for the operator.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T16:00:52.5053424Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76519/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76519/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76519/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the new trains due to be introduced during the new franchise agreement with NXET Trains Ltd for rail passenger services on the Essex Thameside line will equipped with accommodation for a train guard.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","204583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76520","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-15","<p>Since July 2009 there have been 61 accidents investigated by the Air Accidents Investigation Branch in the UK involving public transport aircraft. Of these around 70 per cent were as a result of operational causal factors (human factors) and around 30 per cent were as a result of technical causal factors. The Air Accidents Investigation Branch does not attribute any causes to pilot error as they are explicitly required not to apportion blame or liability.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-07-15T15:41:58.3160097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76520/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76520/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","Aviation: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many air accidents in the UK in the last five years arose from (a) pilot error and (b) mechanical breakdown.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","204556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76521","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The standstill period for the Essex Thameside franchise competition has not yet concluded, as such the Department has not signed the new Franchise Agreement and we are not able to confirm this information at this time. An announcement will be made shortly once the Agreement has been signed. There is already a gate at every station on the franchise and all stations have Ticket Vending Machines (with the exception of West Ham, which is managed by Transport for London). Additional ticket validation will be provided at Dagenham Dock to support step free access at that station.</p><p> </p><p />","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T16:11:58.8470017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76521/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76521/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many new (a) automatic ticket gates and (b) ticket vending machines will be introduced at stations on the Essex Thameside route under the terms of the new franchise agreement with NXET Trains Ltd for rail passenger services.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","204587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76522","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The standstill period for the Essex Thameside franchise competition has not yet concluded, as such the Department has not signed the new Franchise Agreement and we are not able to confirm this information at this time. An announcement will be made shortly once the Agreement has been signed.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T15:52:29.2919253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76522/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76522/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of the planned investment in stations on the Essex Thameside line during the new franchise agreement with NXET Trains Ltd will be funded by the (a) franchisee, (b) Network Rail and (c) the public sector in each case.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","204532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76523","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>Staffing on the franchise is a matter for the operator. The operator must act within the regulatory environment of the railway, which includes safety obligations under their license to operate (granted by the Office of Rail Regulation).</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T16:10:51.2578156Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76523/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76523/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what safeguards there are in the new franchise agreement on the Essex Thameside line with NXET Trains Ltd against unsafe reductions in staff over the life of the agreement.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","204586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76524","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>Staffing is a matter for the operator; as such no discussions have been held between the Secretary of State for Transport and NXET Trains Limited and minimum levels of staffing have not been specified.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-07-14T16:01:54.329097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76524/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76524/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-08","London, Tilbury and Southend Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with NXET Trains Ltd about minimum levels of (a) on-train, (b) station and (c) ticket office staffing levels in each year of the new franchise agreement for rail passenger services on the Essex Thameside line; and what current staffing levels are in each such category on the line.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","204584"
