"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76539","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-07-14T11:55:13.42","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76539/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76539/answer","PQ204631.pdf","PQ204631.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76539/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-08","Jobseeker's Allowance: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment his Department has made of the proportion of young people who left and subsequently returned to claiming jobseeker's allowance within six months in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","204631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76540","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-07-15","<p /> <p /> <p>Universal Credit is currently only available for new claims. Migration will be part of the future delivery plans which were announced in the written ministerial statement made by the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, my Rt. Hon. Friend the Member for Chingford and Woodford Green, Iain Duncan Smith, Official Report, 5 December 2013, column. 65WS.</p><p> </p><p>The Department recognises the advantages of data sharing to help both landlords and the Department deliver their objectives and this will be considered as part of our overall test and learn approach.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-07-15T15:10:15.6604225Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76540/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76540/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-08","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what processes his Department has agreed to enable housing associations to be informed when tenants migrate to universal credit.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","204415"
