"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65969","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-14","<p>Much of the legal advice given to the Department in connection with cases relating to the release of information under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 is provided by the Department's own directly employed legal advisers. No records are kept which would allow us separately to identify the cost of internal advice on Freedom of Information Act matters.</p><p>Where appropriate, the Department also obtains external litigation services in connection with such cases by instructing the Treasury Solicitor's Department. It would be very difficult to identify from the information held by the Department in respect of payments for external legal services, payments in respect of cases relating to the Freedom of Information Act 2000. The costs of trying to collate this information for each of the past 5 years would be disproportionate.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-07-14T16:05:03.273808Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65969/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65969/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-07","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much his Department spent on legal fees in cases relating to the release of information requested under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65970","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Information on the size of organisations offering Apprenticeships is presented in the <em>Apprenticeship Evaluation: Employer</em> research publication:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apprenticeships-evaluation-employer" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apprenticeships-evaluation-employer</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We do not separately measure the number of apprenticeship starts in the public, private and voluntary sectors.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-07-10T14:46:03.3949032Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65970/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65970/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-07","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of apprenticeships commenced in the last 12 months were with (a) small and medium-sized enterprises, (b) larger firms, (c) public sector employers and (d) voluntary sector employers.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","204315"
