"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65979","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>The Prime Minister's Office forms part of the Cabinet Office. In common with other departments, the Cabinet Office pays fees to the Treasury Solicitor's Department for legal advice on a range of issues. The proportion of those fees which relates to the Freedom of Information Act 2000 is not recorded.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","204306","2014-07-10T16:17:01.5527608Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65979/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65979/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much his Department spent on legal fees in cases relating to the release of information requested under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65980","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Prime Minister holds a wide range of events for a range of sectors in the UK economy and meets leaders from all areas of industry. The creative industries employ nearly 1.7 million people and are worth £70 billion to the UK economy, and the Prime Minister is keen to find out how we can do better still in this area. The cost of the reception for approximately 400 guests from across film, music and theatre was £8,860.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","204444","2014-07-14T16:37:04.5256595Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65980/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65980/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Arts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the cost to the public purse was (a) in total, (b) of wine served at, (c) of food served at and (d) of catering staff working at the Best of British Creative Industries reception on 30 June 2014; and which ministers attended that event.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","204246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65981","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-07-10","<p>Growth Deals are negotiated between the Government and Local Enterprise Partnerships. It was for every Local Enterprise Partnership to determine who to contact in advance of the announcement of their Deal.</p><p>I wrote to all hon. Members with constituencies in England on the morning of 7 July, the day of the Growth Deals announcement, setting out full details of the Growth Deal in their area.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-07-10T16:31:07.2523648Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65981/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65981/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-07-07","Local Enterprise Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what guidance the Minister of State for Cities and Constitution has given to local enterprise partnerships on informing (a) district councils and (b) hon. Members about Growth Deal schemes before briefing the media; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","204251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65982","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>As was the case under previous administrations details of internal discussions are not normally disclosed.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-07-10T16:07:17.4601129Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65982/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65982/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Recruitment: Northern Ireland Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what discussions officials from his Department have held with their counterparts in the Northern Ireland Office about that Department accepting placements from the Civil Service fast stream programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65983","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p><p>We encourage all users of public services to go to our award-winning <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>, the official website for government information and services.</p><p>The Cabinet Office is working with Google and other search engine providers to address the problem of misleading websites advertising on their search engines. Work with other bodies such as the Advertising Standards Authority (ASA), the National Trading Standards Board (NTSB) and Which? continues to raise awareness of this issue and ensures action is taken where appropriate.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","204213","2014-07-10T16:15:23.9898214Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65983/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65983/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps his Department is taking to tackle copycat websites which are charging for free Government services.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","204211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65984","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p><p>We encourage all users of public services to go to our award-winning <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>, the official website for government information and services.</p><p>The Cabinet Office is working with Google and other search engine providers to address the problem of misleading websites advertising on their search engines. Work with other bodies such as the Advertising Standards Authority (ASA), the National Trading Standards Board (NTSB) and Which? continues to raise awareness of this issue and ensures action is taken where appropriate.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","204211","2014-07-10T16:15:24.052322Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65984/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65984/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent meetings he has had with internet search engine companies on steps to tackle copycat websites which are charging for free Government services.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","204213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65985","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>ThePrime Minister announced in January 2014 that that this would be the first government in modern history to reduce overall domestic regulation for business while in office. As part of this, he announced that the Red Tape Challenge programme had identified over 3,000 regulations to scrap or improve, delivering estimated savings to UK businesses of over £850m per year by the end of the Parliament. Analysis of the impact of the deregulatory reforms on a geographical basis has not been developed.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-07-14T16:08:26.3998429Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65985/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65985/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Business: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of savings to businesses in (a) the UK, (b) the Thames Valley and (c) Windsor constituency as a result of the Red Tape Challenge.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","204115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65986","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-15","<p>The Government deplores the use of deceptive practices to recover loans. The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) is the regulator responsible for the conduct of banks. It is for the FCA rather than UKFI to consider whether to take action against banks in relation to debt recovery practices.</p><p> </p><p>It is the responsibility of the banks involved to respond to any concerns raised by customers or regulators.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The role of UK Financial Investments Ltd (UKFI) is to manage the Government's shareholdings. As an engaged shareholder, UKFI acts to ensure that the banks have sound long-term strategies which produce value for the taxpayer, and that they are effectively managed and properly governed. However, it does not interfere in day-to-day operations.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-07-15T14:03:29.0031961Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65986/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65986/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-07","Business: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will request UK Financial Investments Ltd to investigate the reasons why banks in receipt of financial support from the public purse have used deceptive practices to recover loans through sending of the letters purporting to be from law firms which do not exist.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","204120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65987","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-07-10T16:13:13.043117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65987/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65987/answer","PQ204217.pdf","PQ204217.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65987/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-07","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the aggregate household debt was in the final quarter of the 2013-14 financial year.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","204217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65988","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-10","<p>The Government has no intention of introducing a tax on derelict land. The Government does not believe that increasing the cost of holding derelict land would be an effective way to incentivise development. The Government is instead focusing on other more effective measures to address stalled sites such as introducing a right of appeal against economically unviable affordable housing (section 106) obligations, and incentivising the development of derelict land through Land Remediation Relief.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-07-10T13:55:34.0839944Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65988/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65988/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-07","Derelict Land: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy to introduce a derelict land tax.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","204221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65989","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-15","<p>The Government does not collect data on the number of applications participating lenders receive for mortgages supported by the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Government publishes quarterly official statistics relating to the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme. The first of these were published on 29 May 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This report, along with accompanying tables, can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-07-15T14:55:56.3756854Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65989/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65989/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-07","Help to Buy Scheme: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many applications have been submitted from Northern Ireland for the Help to Buy mortgage guarantee scheme since January 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65990","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-10","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) monitors the performance of its contractor regularly under a range of provisions. Commercial discussions between HMRC and its suppliers are confidential.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-07-10T13:54:11.3131001Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65990/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65990/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-07","Mapeley","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the (a) compliance and (b) performance of Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited following HM Revenue and Custom's last audit of such compliance and performance of Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited in respect of the Annual PM Schedule under 17.1(a) of the Private Finance Initiative contract between HM Revenue and Customs and Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","204244"
