"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65998","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>There are currently 26 approved professions across the Civil Service. The majority of development courses available to support the continuous professional development of those concerned are provided through the central training portal, Civil Service Learning. This means all available course costs are centrally negotiated, ensuring economies of scale and best value for Government. The individual cost of these courses range in price depending on profession and the training require and it would involve disproportionate cost to provide the detailed information requested.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-07-14T14:36:23.7781378Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65998/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65998/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-07","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what professional development courses are made available to staff of his Department; and what the cost to the public purse is of each such course.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65999","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>Selective licensing allows local authorities to license all privately rented housing in a designated area that suffers from low housing demand and/or significant anti-social behaviour. The Department does not routinely collect information on the number or extent of licensing schemes although local authorities were asked on a one-off voluntary basis to provide this information last year. 194 local authorities responded, of which 14 had introduced licensing. While an assessment of the impact of licensing on private sector rents has not been undertaken, we believe that licensing puts unnecessary extra costs on good landlords, thereby pushing up rents, and reduces choice.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-07-14T15:50:54.1314167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65999/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65999/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-07","Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the introduction of selective licensing in relevant areas and the level of private-sector rates; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Richard Ottaway","Croydon South","Sir Richard Ottaway","204242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66000","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>This information could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-07-22T15:33:57.2038399Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66000/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66000/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-07","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department spent on legal fees in cases relating to the release of information requested under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66001","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>We plan to publish an analysis of the replies and proposed next steps, including any decision that may be made on restrictions of borough wide licensing schemes, in the Summer.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-07-14T15:49:53.9969666Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66001/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66001/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-07","Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when his Department plans to publish the conclusions of its review of property conditions in the private rented sector; and whether his Department plans to restrict borough-wide selective licensing schemes.","false","Biography information for Sir Richard Ottaway","Croydon South","Sir Richard Ottaway","204243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66002","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>This information could only be provided at disproportional cost. Details of ministerial overseas travel and meetings with external organisations are routinely published every quarter and information can be accessed on the Department's web page via the following link:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data</a></p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-07-14T16:00:47.5074703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66002/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66002/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66002/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-07","Air Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, on what occasions each Minister within his Department has taken domestic flights on official business since May 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66003","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>Since January 2010 three applications for onshore wind development have been called in by the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government. The three applications have all been called in during 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All three followed requests by local or neighbouring Members of Parliament to call in the applications.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-07-14T15:52:55.7962308Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66003/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66003/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66003/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-07","Wind Power: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many onshore wind development planning applications that had been considered by local planning authorities were subsequently called in by his Department in each of the five years.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","204131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66004","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-10","<p>I am happy to discuss this, but the government remains committed to the all-seater policy. We remain of the belief that all-seater stadiums are the safest and best way for fans to watch football and have brought a more diverse audience to the game in the last 20 years.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-07-10T14:25:38.2231189Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66004/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66004/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66004/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Football: Sportsgrounds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will discuss with the Football Association the development of safe standing areas in Premiership Club grounds.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","204214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66005","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>Yes.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-07-14T13:16:41.7823451Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66005/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66005/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66005/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Mobile Phones: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether mobile data services will be expanded in Northern Ireland as part of the Mobile Infrastructure Project.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66006","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>DCMS officials and our delivery partner Arqiva are continually reviewing potential locations for masts with the intention of providing coverage to as many premises as possible. Various challenges will have an impact on the number of premises we can reach and completion dates for individual masts, such as finding a suitable and sensitive location for a mast, obtaining planning permission, and ensuring masts can connect back into the existing network.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-07-14T13:17:44.5696861Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66006/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66006/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66006/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Mobile Phones: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of how many households in Northern Ireland will benefit from each phase of the Mobile Infrastructure Project; and what the current expected date of completion is for each phase of that project in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66007","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-10","<p><strong>This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</strong></p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-07-10T14:28:16.9193334Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66007/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66007/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Air Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, on what occasions each Minister within his Department has taken domestic flights on official business since May 2010.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66008","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>We are investing up to £150m to provide coverage across the UK through the Mobile Infrastructure Project. Funding is not allocated by country or area. Funding is provided for potential sites on a case by case basis, with sites selected according to the number of homes and businesses for which signal could be provided balanced against the cost to build and run each individual site.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-07-14T13:18:30.61689Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66008/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66008/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Mobile Phones: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what level of funding has been allocated by his Department to projects in Northern Ireland under the Mobile Infrastructure Project.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204239"
