"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66010","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Tour De France Grand Depart was a resounding success and was extremely well supported in communities along all three stages, including the East of England and Essex. UK Sport is supporting the production of an economic impact report covering the main locations on the route and this will be made available later this year.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-07-14T11:09:29.0968747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66010/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66010/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Tour de France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the financial benefit to (a) Essex and (b) the East of England arising from the launch of the Tour de France.","false","Biography information for Robert Halfon","Harlow","Robert Halfon","204361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66011","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>DCMS has interpreted ‘Professional Development courses' as formal training which relates directly to a professional specialism for which a qualification, specific training or membership is required.</p><p>Along with other government departments, DCMS has access to a range of professional development courses that are made available to staff through the Civil Service Learning portal, a centrally run service. These include courses relating to professions such as Finance, Procurement, Human Resources, Knowledge Management, policy and Project Delivery. Applications for professional development courses for DCMS staff are approved against the DCMS Learning &amp; Development budget.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-07-14T11:08:40.1798594Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66011/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66011/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what professional development courses are made available to staff of his Department; and what the cost to the public purse is of each such course.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66012","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Department does not ask this question or collect this information.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-07-14T11:07:38.5285296Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66012/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66012/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-07","Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many senior civil servants appointed to positions in his Department since 2010 were previously (a) political appointees within that Department and (b) employed by a political party.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204320"
