"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66014","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The Military Aviation Authority has made no such recommendation.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-10T13:43:07.8203927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66014/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66014/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66014/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-07","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Military Aviation Authority recommended that F-35B BK-3 should not transit the Atlantic Ocean in time for the Royal International Air Tattoo.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","204371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66015","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The C-17 aircraft sustainment package is a contract between the United States Government and the Boeing Corporation. Through the Foreign Military Sales programme, the United Kingdom utilises this contract to support our fleet of eight C-17 aircraft. The United States Government has agreed to extend our participation in the contract for a further three years at an estimated cost of up to $250 million.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-10T15:35:09.3091804Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66015/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66015/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66015/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-07","C17 Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost was of the extension of the C-17 Globemaster III sustainment package contract; and for how long that contract will run.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","204369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66016","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>There have been no occasions when the Military Aviation Authority have recommended that F-35B be grounded or restricted in operations.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-10T13:40:09.7384654Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66016/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66016/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66016/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-07","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions the Military Aviation Authority has recommended that the F-35B be (a) grounded and (b) restricted in operations; what the reason was for each such recommendation; and what the duration of the grounding or restriction was in each such case.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","204370"
