"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66143","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>DFID has decentralised responsibility for training and professional development to line managers and Heads of Profession. The information requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-14T16:15:31.591461Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66143/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66143/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what professional development courses are made available to staff of her Department; and what the cost to the public purse is of each such course.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66144","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-14","<p>We have no central report readily available detailing the senior civil servants who have been appointed since 2010 and who were previously (a) political appointees within DFID and (b) employed by a political party. This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost</p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-14T16:12:36.5814806Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66144/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66144/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many senior civil servants appointed to positions in her Department since 2010 were previously (a) political appointees within that Department and (b) employed by a political party.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66145","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Since January 2013, DFID Ministers have made the following domestic visits on official business:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Secretary of State (Rt Hon Justine Greening MP)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>17 January 2013 – Visit to the DFID office in East Kilbride</p><p> </p><p>28 January 2013 – Regional Cabinet in Leeds</p><p> </p><p>20 May 2013 – Regional Visit to Watford</p><p> </p><p>27 June 2013 – Regional Visit to Dartford</p><p> </p><p>24 October 2013 – Visit to the DFID office in East Kilbride</p><p> </p><p>20 November 2013 – Regional Visit to Brighton and Hastings</p><p> </p><p>11 February 2014 – Regional Visit to Pudsey</p><p> </p><p>24 February 2014 – Regional Visit to Edinburgh and Regional Cabinet in Aberdeen</p><p> </p><p>1 May 2014 – Regional Visit to Birmingham and Warwick</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Minister of State (Rt Hon Alan Duncan MP)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>6 March 2014 – Regional Visit to Aberdeen</p><p> </p><p>1 May 2014 – Visit to the DFID office in East Kilbride and Glasgow</p><p> </p><p>2 May 2014 – Regional visit to Edinburgh</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State (Lynne Featherstone MP)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>4 February 2013 – Regional Visit to Winchester</p><p> </p><p>10 June 2013 – Visit to the DFID office in East Kilbride.</p><p> </p><p>2 July 2013 – Regional Visit to Milton Keynes</p><p> </p><p>9 October 2013 – Regional Visit to Bristol</p><p> </p><p>24 February 2014 – Regional Visit to Birmingham and Ruby</p><p> </p><p>26 February 2014 – Visit to the DFID office in East Kilbride</p><p> </p><p>17 March 2014 – Visit to the DFID office in East Kilbride</p><p> </p><p>29 June 2014 – Regional Visit to Edinburgh</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-10T15:52:00.5561436Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66145/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66145/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Domestic Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2014, Official Report, column 681W, on official visits, what domestic visits each of the Ministers of her Department has made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","204375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66146","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>DFID, along with other aid agencies on the ground in Rakhine, are working to ensure a coordinated response. Our bilateral humanitarian support in Rakhine includes assistance for water, sanitation, and nutrition. Support is provided to both communities. We have not provided bilateral support for medicine and healthcare provision, but ECHO and UN agencies to whom we provide core funding, are. In addition to the delivery of aid, DFID and the FCO continue to advocate at all levels of Government for establishment of conditions which allow for unhindered humanitarian access.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-14T16:06:08.3185253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66146/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66146/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that displaced Rohingya Muslims have access to basic medicine and healthcare provision.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","204170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66147","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Incidents of substantiated fraud are set out in both the Department's Annual Report and, where appropriate, in the notes of the Annual Accounts.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-10T15:41:40.7449345Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66147/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66147/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Developing Countries: Fraud and Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many reports of fraud or corrupt practices her Department has received (a) in writing and (b) through the development tracker website in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","204163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66148","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>The Secretary of State has final approval of all GPAF funding decisions. All grants approved by the Secretary of State are subject to satisfactory completion of pre-grant due diligence.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-10T15:40:31.205467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66148/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66148/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether decisions to award funding under the Global Poverty Action Fund were made by the Civil Society Department, Policy and Research Division of her Department or by Triple Line Consulting Ltd.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","204162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66149","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>FCO and DFID staff monitor the humanitarian situation in Rakhine State closely and visit frequently. Whilst there have been improvements to humanitarian operations following the severe disruptions caused by attacks on UN and international NGO premises in March, many vulnerable communities, including the Rohingya, remain under-served. The UK is providing bilateral humanitarian support in Rakhine to all communities affected by the humanitarian situation there, as well as support through core contributions to multilateral agencies.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-10T15:43:04.527743Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66149/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66149/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the humanitarian situation of displaced Rohingya Muslims in Burma.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","204198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66150","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p>Full information on Conflict Pool programmes managed by DFID can be found on the online Development Tracker at:</p><p><a href="http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/</a></p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-10T15:37:50.4184095Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66150/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66150/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Conflict Pool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department has spent from the Conflict Pool in each country in each year since its launch.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","204161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66151","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>To date, the UK government has contributed £897,000 to the Ebola Virus Disease response in Sierra Leone and Liberia through multilateral partners and the DFID bilateral programme. In addition, DFID is finalizing arrangements to send out three Public Health England disease control specialists to Sierra Leone to support the response. We are working with the World Health Organisation (WHO) and national government agencies to closely monitor the situation and help guide any additional response by DFID in-country and in the region.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-10T15:50:41.9615713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66151/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66151/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","West Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what additional support she is providing to authorities in West Africa to help them with the recent ebola outbreak.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","204215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66152","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Full information on funding to the Rapid Response Facility can be found on the online Development Tracker at: <a href="http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following amounts have been spent in countries through the Rapid Response Facility since its launch:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Sierra Leone: £2m</p><p> </p><p>India: £2.3m</p><p> </p><p>Philippines: £8m</p><p> </p><p>South Sudan: £6m</p><p> </p><p>Bosnia: £0.3m</p><p> </p><p>Iraq: £2m</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-10T15:37:04.2244549Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66152/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66152/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Disaster Relief","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department has spent from the Rapid Response Facility in each country in each year since its launch.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","204160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66153","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>Triple Line Consulting Ltd is the contracted Fund Manager of the Global Poverty Action Fund. To manage the Global Poverty Action Fund, Triple Line Consulting Ltd has been paid:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>£0.2m in 2010/11</p><p> </p><p>£0.8m in 2011/12</p><p> </p><p>£0.7m in 2012/13</p><p> </p><p>£1.3m in 2013/14</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-10T15:35:59.5060465Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66153/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66153/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Triple Line Consulting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much has been paid to Triple Line Consulting Ltd for the management and running of the Global Poverty Action Fund in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","204159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66154","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The scholarships offered by the Commonwealth Scholarship Commission in the UK are for citizens of other Commonwealth countries to study in the United Kingdom, or for UK qualifications. UK citizens resident in the United Kingdom are not eligible for these awards.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-14T16:08:02.3108816Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66154/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66154/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Commonwealth Scholarships Programme: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what work the Commonwealth Scholarship Commission does to promote the availability of its scholarships to students resident in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66155","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>Public Health England and NHS England are working jointly to assess the responses to the consultation on the draft strategy and the impact of these proposals on the National Health Service. They will also be agreeing the arrangements for publication.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-14T12:31:17.2523043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66155/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66155/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-07","Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the Collaborative TB Strategy for England will be jointly published and delivered by Public Health England and NHS England.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","204226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66156","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>In financial year 2013/14 DFID provided £34.6m to Oxfam GB for their international humanitarian response programmes and long term development work. DFID provides no support to Oxfam's UK programmes.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-07-14T16:14:01.27382Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66156/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66156/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-07","Oxfam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much public funding her Department gave directly or indirectly to Oxfam in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","204126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66157","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-10","<p>The Transforming Rehabilitation Programme is opening up the market to a diverse range of new providers, so that we can harness the best that the private and voluntary sectors have to offer to reduce reoffending. The competition to award contracts to run the new Community Rehabilitation Companies is ongoing and in June we received bids from potential providers. We are committed to rolling out these important reforms by 2015.</p><p>The Government has been clear that we want to see a diverse market delivering probation services, rather than being dominated by just a few providers. We have set a market share restriction whereby bidders can win a maximum of 25% of market share based on the indicative contract values set out in the competition documentation. Bidders will be allowed to win multiple contracts up to the point at which their market share cap would be breached subject to meeting any other requirements set out by the Authority.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","204268","2014-07-10T16:24:35.7341008Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66157/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66157/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Community Rehabilitation Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department will impose a cap on the number of contracts any one bidder can be awarded to undertake the work of the 21 community rehabilitation companies.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","204265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66158","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-10","<p>The Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority (CICA) publishes data about the reasons applications are ineligible in its annual reports at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=criminal-injuries-compensation-authority&amp;publication_type=corporate-reports" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=criminal-injuries-compensation-authority&amp;publication_type=corporate-reports</a></p><p> </p><p>The published figures show the number of times each refusal reason was used. That does not reflect an accurate total of ineligible cases because some cases are ineligible for multiple reasons. The accurate total of ineligible cases for the calendar years specified is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Ineligible cases</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>27,302</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>23,316</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>25,385</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>23,783</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014 (up to 8 July)</p></td><td><p>11,309</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>I have placed records showing why each of these cases was ineligible in the House of Commons library. CICA uses injuries as the basis for a payment so very few ineligible cases have injuries recorded for them. Where an injury has been assessed and entered on the case file it is included in the records provided.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-07-10T16:09:26.7572707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66158/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66158/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Criminal Injuries Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many applications for compensation were rejected by the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014 to date; and if he will list in each case the injuries sustained by the applicant and the reason for the application being refused.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","204261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66159","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-10","<p>As of 8July 2014, the relevant media organisations inform us that 117 hearings have been recorded since legislation was passed on the 31 October 2013 to enable live television broadcasting from the Court of Appeal.</p><p> </p><p>The BBC, ITN, Sky and the Press Association determine which cases should be filmed and it is for those individual media organisations to decide what should be broadcast, and when. No information about how many cases are broadcast, or how many minutes of coverage, is held by the Ministry of Justice.</p><p> </p><p>Court broadcasting gives the public the opportunity to see and hear the decisions of judges in their own words and is a step towards achieving our aim of having an open and transparent justice system.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","204267","2014-07-10T16:48:30.8676962Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66159/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66159/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Court of Appeal: Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Court of Appeal hearings have been televised since cameras were first allowed in court.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","204262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66160","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-14","<p>The requested information is not held centrally and would need to be obtained and collated through enquiries at each prison. This would require a manual search of all cells and all other areas where books might be held. This would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-07-14T07:59:49.4341081Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66160/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66160/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Prisons: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many books there are in HM Prison (a) Leeds and (b) Wakefield.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","204166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66161","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>We have not instructed Wates, the preferred bidder for the design and build of the pathfinder Secure College, to include a segregation unit in the designs.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-07-15T08:57:44.089093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66161/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66161/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Secure Colleges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether secure colleges will contain segregation units.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","204372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66162","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-22","<p>We are unable to provide the number of civil servants appointed to the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) who were previously (a) political appointees and (b) employed by a political party. As this information is not held centrally, to collate this information as a whole would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-07-22T16:38:48.2597719Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66162/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66162/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many senior civil servants appointed to positions in his Department since 2010 were previously (a) political appointees within that Department and (b) employed by a political party.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66163","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-10","<p>The number of self-inflicted deaths in prison custody for the last 10 years is published in the Safety in Custody statistical bulletin which is available at <a title="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/safety-in-custody-statistics" href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/safety-in-custody-statistics" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/safety-in-custody-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We are working hard to manage the levels of self-harm in prison and are carefully investigating the rise in self-inflicted deaths.</p><p> </p><p>We are applying strenuous efforts to learn from each one and providing further resources and support to prisons to help support their safer custody work.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-07-10T16:12:02.6140374Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66163/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66163/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Prisoners: Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners committed suicide in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","204365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66164","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-10","<p>The legal profession is independent of Government. The Legal Services Board and approved regulators are responsible for determining the qualification requirements, ongoing training, quality assurance and other regulatory requirements for legal services providers, such as solicitors, barristers and legal executives.</p><p> </p><p>In criminal cases, there is a range of training and materials available to all advocates in relation to cases involving vulnerable witnesses, including children, much of it available through the Advocates' Gateway. The Bar Council and Law Society have announced a new initiative to train defence lawyers on cases involving vulnerable witnesses, and I welcome this.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-07-10T16:46:04.0076029Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66164/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66164/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Courts: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will introduce mandatory training for lawyers dealing with children.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","204364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66165","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-14","<p>Professional development, in the form of formal learning, is available to all members of staff within the Ministry of Justice and processes are in place to ensure that where there is a business and development need learning can be accessed. There are currently 22 professions across the civil service and each will have their own framework of qualifications.</p><p> </p><p>In order to answer the question in detail we will need to contact every profession, request the framework and then identify the costs for each qualification. In addition we will need to interrogate the Civil Service Learning portal to identify each professions qualifications and costs. This information is not readily available and is not held centrally and therefore would incur disproportionate cost to obtain.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-07-14T13:19:34.7736015Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66165/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66165/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what professional development courses are made available to staff of his Department; and what the cost to the public purse is of each such course.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66166","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not centrally record the legal fees incurred by the Department in obtaining legal advice in relation to requests for information under the Freedom of Information Act 2000. To obtain this information from across the Ministry would incur a disproportionate cost.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-07-14T14:02:18.4681199Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66166/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66166/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-07","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much his Department spent on legal fees in cases relating to the release of information requested under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","204281"
