"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66175","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost. Details of all Ministerial overseas travel is published on a quarterly basis.</p><p>I should add that on coming to office in May 2010, my predecessor ended the chartering of a private jet for routine travel between London and Belfast which had been the practice of previous Secretaries of State, including those in the last Labour Government. This has saved the taxpayer considerable sums of money.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","204300","2014-07-14T14:23:13.3224151Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66175/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66175/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-07","Domestic Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2014, Official Report, columns 724-5W, on official visits, what domestic visits each of the Ministers of her Department has made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","204373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66176","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>I very much support the promotion of the Northern Ireland healthcare sector to overseas markets and supporting healthcare partnerships between Northern Ireland and overseas healthcare providers and I stand ready to work alongside Northern Ireland Executive Ministers in this regard.</p><p>But given that these relate to devolved matters in Northern Ireland, I would expect these discussions to be conducted primarily between the relevant Northern Ireland Executive Departments and Healthcare UK, rather than through the Northern Ireland Office.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-10T14:51:05.6044154Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66176/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66176/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-07","Healthcare UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent discussions she has had with the Chief Executive of Healthcare UK to ensure that business, academia, health and public sector organisations in Northern Ireland are included in Healthcare UK's priorities for 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66177","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>My Department follows the Ministry of Justice guidance on work experience placements, which is based on Cabinet Office guidance.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-14T14:16:33.2131565Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66177/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66177/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-07","Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to her Answer of 3 July 2014, Official Report, column 713W, on work experience, whether her Department follows Cabinet Office guidance on work experience placements.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66178","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-10","<p> </p><p>I replied to the hon Gentleman on 8 July.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-10T12:17:43.0672955Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66178/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/66178/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-07","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, when she intends to reply to the letter from the hon. Member for Bury South  constituency of 12 June 2014 on a youth summit on building a shared future.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204146"
